==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bunsen cell
<hw>Bun"sen cell</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A
zinc-carbon cell in which the zinc (amalgamated) is surrounded by dilute
sulphuric acid, and the carbon by nitric acid or a chromic acid mixture,
the two plates being separated by a porous cup.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bunt</ent>⟦br⟧
